Chase Jones (2024-2059), also known by the stage name Yung Jones, is an Australian rapper.

== Early life (2024-2041) ==
Chase Jones was born in 2024 in Adelaide, South Australia. His mother is [[Sophie Robinson]].

He dated Georgia Rogers (b. 2024) from 2034-2040. 

He dated Tahlia Tran-Jones (2024-2059) from 2040-2041. In 2041, they had a daughter named Amelia.

== Music (2042-2059) ==
In 2042, Jones graduated from secondary school. He signed as a singer for Back Door Entertainment and adopted the stage name “Yung Jones”. He released his debut album, “Get Cheddar or Die Trying”.

In 2043, he became famous and released his second album, “My Divine Dark Twisted Delusion”. He started dating Tahlia Tran-Jones.

In 2059, he was murdered.

